UID:TS1-4EDD4519-CE94-4D05-B1D6-067B4D83BAD9
DTSTART:20180911T130000
DTEND:20180911T170000
SUMMARY:+Faculty meeting (extended)+
DESCRIPTION:<2018-09-11 Tue 13:00-17:00>
CATEGORIES:PSE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T052155Z
UID:TS1-AAA60A68-A640-4BF8-A5DB-3E5AEBEC81C5
DTSTART:20181030T120000
DTEND:20181030T133000
SUMMARY:Faculty meeting
DESCRIPTION:<2018-10-30 Tue 12:00-13:30>\n:location: Conte A524\n\n\nAttend
 ees: Bryan Coughlin\, Reika Katsumata\, Laura Bradley\, Al Crosby\,\nDave 
 Hoagland\, Greg Tew\, Muthukumar\, Greg Grason\, Sam Gido\, Harry\nBermude
 z\, Jim Watkins\, Maria Santore\, Ken Carter\, Ryan Hayward\n\nMinutes fro
 m 10/2 faculty meeting were circulated and reviewed by all.\nA motion to a
 pprove the minutes was made\, seconded\, and voted\nunanimously to accept.
 \n\nPSE Graduate Student Guidelines was the first topic of discussion.\nMi
 lestones were discussed in terms of timeline for the various\nmilestones w
 ere discussed.  A number of items associated with review\nand potential ch
 anges were discussed.  Some of these include the\naddition of an additiona
 l separate milestone that the student’s\nAdvisory Committee be completed b
 y some set time (e.g.\, end of the\nsecond year) to provide additional gui
 dance during their career.\nOther concepts including Individual Developmen
 t Plans (IDP)\, and\nexpectations associated with each of the milestones w
 ere also\ndiscussed.\n\nAfter discussion\, it was decided to table the thi
 s until the December\nfaculty meeting since more pressing issues needed to
  be addresses\nwithin the allotted timeframe.\n\nNext\, an Advisor Change 
 Policy developed by the GPD was presented to\nthe department for review an
 d discussion.  It was noted that the\nfaculty climate committee had review
 ed it prior to its submission to\nthe rest of the faculty.  Certain edits 
 and clarifications were noted\nand will be incorporated by the GPD.  After
 ward\, it was agreed that it\nbe forwarded to the PSE Climate Committee to
  obtain their feedback.\n\nThe final agenda item on the list was the “Town
  hall Meeting”\nscheduled for next Wednesday (Nov. 7th) was discussed.  As
 pects\nassociated with various details of the meeting including who would\
 nfacilitate the meeting to what would be appropriate agenda items are\napp
 ropriate.  It was suggested that a website be set up to solicit\ntopics to
  be addressed anonymously prior to the meeting for those who\nmay feel rel
 uctant bringing it up during the meeting.  Bryan will\ncoordinate the soli
 citation of topics using this approach.
CATEGORIES:PSE
END:VEVENT
